The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | FIH is happy
                                                                                                                       7                                      FIH is happy
                      
	New Delhi: The International Hockey Federation (FIH) Tuesday expressed satisfaction on the preparation for next months World Cup, and said the venue for the event, Major Dhyanchand National Stadium is one of the best ones in the world.         
	An FIH delegation, led by president Leandro Negre, and Indian Olympic Association chief Suresh Kalmadi carried out an inspection of the stadium, where the event would be held from February 28 to March 13.         
	2010 is a very important year for FIH. We have two World Cups, first the mens World Cup here and then the womens World Cup in Argentina. We are spending a lot of time to make both the events a success, Negre told reporters.         
	We are very happy with how things are moving here. The stadium is beautiful, he added. (PTI)                                                                                                                     
